@node play "The game: Installation/Playing"

                             Installation

  The installation is very simple, just place "Pyramid" where you
want on your hard drive, floppy disk, Ram Disk, etc. No other files
or Libraries are needed.

NOTE: As I am not sure of this game's 'behaviour' on a stock 68000
      Amiga. For now, until somebody confirms that Pyramid runs
      fine on a 68000 machine, this game will require an Amiga
      with a 68020 or faster processor... sorry!

                             How to play?

  At the start of a game, your location is at the lower left of the
pyramid; your position is indicated by a white human figure and is
always located in the center of the display. To move, click on any
space or tile in the general direction you want to go, if you are
in front or on top of a ladder, click on a space above or below
your position to go in the desired direction. If the move is
possible, the display will be updated at the new position. Note
that you can also use the cursor keys to move in the pyramid.

  Pharaoh's tomb is located at the topmost level of the pyramid. If
you get there, the game ends and displays how many moves it took to
get there, then the game will create a new pyramid to explore...

  You can restart the game anytime by clicking on the @{b}New Game@{ub}
button.

  Have fun!

  You can quit the game by clicking on the main window's close
button or by pressing on the 'Esc' key.

